On Tue, Aug 24, 1999 at 12:27:33PM +0200, Petr Sebor wrote:
> I have observed that this one happened with the original TOOLs disk
> I got with the drive and I can confirm that it locates this disk always
> as sda1, not sda4... huh.. strange, I have always thought that the
> magic 4 is a hw issue... Ok, never mind...
Zip disks have partition tables.  When you buy the disks they are usually
set up to have 1 partition which is partition number 4.  You can use fdisk
to partition it however you want to.  There is nothing that forces it to
be partition number 4.  Do an:
fdisk /dev/sda
and see whats there.
Jim
